[
  "Yusuf Hamied is the non-executive chairman of $2.1 billion (revenue) generics maker Cipla.",
  "Cipla was founded in 1935 by his father Khwaja Abdul Hamied, a disciple of Mahatma Gandhi.",
  "After the patriarch passed away in 1972, Cambridge-educated Hamied and his brother Mustafa inherited the business.",
  "Hamied took on big pharmaceutical companies, offering low-cost generic drugs for diseases such as AIDS, earning the label of drug pirate. \r\n"
]